The paper presents a new solver architecture for answer set programming (ASP) that integrates different algorithm selection approaches and techniques. This makes it relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with solving problems using logic-based methods. The paper also discusses the use of portfolios and pre-solving techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results and performance gains, which are relevant to the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the design and flexibility of the solver architecture, which is relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
